<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 03 at 8:46PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Roanoke, east central Giles, southwestern Craig and northern
Montgomery Counties through 915 PM EDT...
At 845 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Blacksburg, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Blacksburg...
Newport...
Catawba...
Sinking Creek...
Abbott...
Craig Springs...
and Mc Donalds Mill.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
